    key: "A matrix structure organises employees by both function and project, so staff report to two managers simultaneously — a functional manager and a project manager.",
    body: "In a matrix structure, employees belong to their functional department (e.g., Finance, Engineering) but are also assigned to specific project teams. This is common in consulting firms, construction companies, and IT firms in Nigeria.",
